I"<p>ChatGPT launched during the Ides of March, 2023. Right in the middle of my Spring semester at the California College of the Arts. I was eager to share it with my class – could I help Interaction Design students realize a gesture based interface?</p>

<p>I was honored to sum up the whole experience in 5 minutes at the Long Now Ignite talks:</p>

<iframe width="560" height="315" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/M0WB-hAPqxU?si=sqzA6MU8zKRR6Dc6" title="YouTube video player" frameborder="0" allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share" allowfullscreen=""></iframe>

<p>The answer, of course, was a resounding “yes”. But I hasten to add that teaching with AI is not easier. Precisely because it’s so capable, AI requires <em>more</em> of teachers and students.</p>

